 2.3 
 
 Panel data models 
 
 The pre-decided and (random/including random data points) edge of something/unexplored area production functions (1) and 
 (4) are defined for thin sliceal data (i.e., data on a thin slice of N 
 firms at some particular time period). If time-series (instances of watching, noticing, or making statements) are 
 available for the sample firms involved, then the data are referred to as 
 panel data. Pitt and Lee (1981) thought about/believed the guess of a (random/including random data points) 
 edge of something/unexplored area production function connected with N firms over T time periods. 
