 were guessed to range from 0.64 to 0.91, with average 0.70. A moving backward 
 of the guessed technical (measures of output versus waste/getting more with less waste) on farm-clearly stated/particular (numbers that change/things that change) pointed to/showed 
 that farming experience, level of education, access to credit and extension 
 contacts had big influences on the difference/different version of the farm (measures of output versus waste/getting more with less waste). 
 Battese and Coelli (1992) applied their panel-data model including 
 time-changing/different firm effects in the analysis of data for paddy farmers in an 
 Indian village who were watched/followed for up to ten years. Given the (detailed descriptions of exactly what is required) of a (random/including random data points) edge of something/unexplored area production function with time-invariant limits/guidelines, the guess of time-invariant technical (measures of output versus waste/getting more with less waste) of the 
 paddy farmers was rejected. However, given that a linear time (popular thing/general way things are going) was 
 included in the (random/including random data points) edge of something/unexplored area model (Dummiesian neutral technical 
 change), then the guess of time-invariant technical (measures of output versus waste/getting more with less waste) was 
 accepted. Also, the (random/including random data points) edge of something/unexplored area production function with the 
 time (popular thing/general way things are going) included was not very different from the average response function (i.e., technical inefficiences could be thought about/believed (not there; not present) 
 from the model. 15 The scientific results were gotten using the computer 
